Program: Omnibus
Title: AIDS a Decade of Despair and Promise
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376k4g
Last Broadcast Date: 03 July 1991
Worldwide eight to ten million adults are estimated to be infected with HIV; by 2000 it could be twenty-five million. A look at how the virus emerged, how it is progressing and who is most at risk.